trans-unit.source: Returns an enumerator that can iterate through the collection.
trans-unit.target: Devolve um enumerador que pode itere através da coleção.

trans-unit.source: Enumerators only allow reading the data in the collection.
trans-unit.target: Enumeradores permitem apenas ao ler os dados na coleção.

trans-unit.source: Enumerators cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
trans-unit.target: Enumeradores não podem ser utilizados para modificar a colecção subjacente.

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first item in the collection.
trans-unit.target: Inicialmente, o enumerador está posicionado antes do primeiro item na coleção.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> also brings the enumerator back to this position.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>também oferece o enumerador novamente para nesta posição.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>

trans-unit.source: At this position, calling <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> throws an exception.
trans-unit.target: AT isto posicionar, chamar <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>emite uma exceção.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you must call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> to advance the enumerator to the first item of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Por conseguinte, tem de chamar <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>para avançar o enumerador para o primeiro item da coleção antes de ler o valor de <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> returns the same object until either <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>Devolve o mesmo objeto até ser <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>ou <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>é chamado.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A></xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the next item.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>Define <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>para o item seguinte.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A></xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: After the end of the collection is passed, the enumerator is positioned after the last item in the collection, and calling <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: Após o final da colecção é passado, o enumerador está posicionado depois do último item na coleção e chamar <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>devolve `false`.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, calling <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> throws an exception.
trans-unit.target: Se a última chamada para <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>devolvido `false`, chamar <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>emite uma exceção.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: To set <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the first item of the collection again, you can call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> followed by <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Para definir <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>o primeiro item da coleção novamente, pode chamar <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>seguido <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: Um enumerador permanece válido desde que a coleção permanece inalterada.

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying or deleting items, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and the next call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> throws an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.
trans-unit.target: Caso sejam feitas alterações à coleção, tais como adicionar, modificar ou eliminar itens, o enumerador está irrevogavelmente inválido e a próxima chamada ou <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>emitir um <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.</xref:System.InvalidOperationException> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the collection is modified between <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> will return the item that it is set to, even if the enumerator is already invalidated.
trans-unit.target: Se a coleção é modificada entre <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>e <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>irá devolver o item que está definido, mesmo que o enumerador já é invalidado.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection; therefore, enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: O enumerador não tem acesso exclusivo à coleção; Por conseguinte, a enumerar através de uma coleção intrinsecamente não é um procedimento seguro para thread.

trans-unit.source: Even when a collection is synchronized, other threads could still modify the collection, which causes the enumerator to throw an exception.
trans-unit.target: Mesmo quando uma coleção está sincronizada, outros threads ainda foi possível modificar a coleção, o que faz com que o enumerador acionar uma excepção.

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can either lock the collection during the entire enumeration or catch the exceptions resulting from changes made by other threads.
trans-unit.target: Para garantir a segurança de thread durante a enumeração, pode bloquear a coleção durante a enumeração de toda ou detetar exceções resultantes das alterações efetuadas por outros threads.
